  "description": "<i>Arrow One</i> is the thirteenth in series of monthly text adventures for multiple systems.<br><br>It's been 3 years now, 3 years since your mission into deep space.  Your name is Adam Trent, explorer, trouble-shooter, and all around good guy for the Federation of Space.  Your journey aboard Arrow One has come to an end: an uncharted planet the council asked you to explore.  Slowly you descend onto this strange new world. <br><br>Upon landing on the alien planet, the player must gain entry to the alien city of Pfitt by impersonating one of its denizens.  Within, the player must learn about the alien culture and language with assistance of the local librarian, and explore the sites within the city. The player needs to gain access to a flying Gooba to travel to another city, where they meet the dying Professor, who asks us to save his daughter in exchange for the code that will destroy the alien supercomputer controlling the planet.  Upon returning with his daughter, the player is able to destroy the computer, eliminating the alien menace and all other technology on the planet.  Then, it is revealed the daughter's name is Eve, and Adam and Eve, stranded on this strange planet, must make a new life for themselves.<br><br>All commands are via 2-word VERB NOUN entries, and game play contains several object puzzles. There is no save and restore feature.",
